I’m not sure if it’s with the authorities knowledge that this is happening, because the last round I went the lady working the counter was extremely rude. Yesterday 16th April I went there, they were opened for once and there were this 3 young girls running the store. I overheard them telling the client before me that they were new and they did not know where things were and to excuse them and only order basic drink options that only had fruits in them. This was very odd for me. My turn came and they took my order and I got my drink. When my drinks was being poured into the cups I realised there were a fair amount left over in the blender. She passed me the drinks and I walked away. After taking a couple of sips I realised that the drinks were very diluted! I walked back and I spoke to a staff called Teha. She was very nice and kind to me. She explained that their freezer is not working and everything has melted and it’s difficult to measure the ingredients. She remade the order for me and it tasted better. I just want to take this opportunity and say to boost please fix your outlet. I will be also writing an email to DPC waterfront management to look into your outlet since it’s been getting poor reviews for a while now. The space can be utilised with better vendors with better services.
